RIYADH: Moroccan pilgrims who have benefited from the Makkah Route initiative praised it as an honor and said it adds to the great efforts made by the Kingdom to improve services provided to pilgrims. The initiative was launched in Morocco at the Mohammed V International Airport in Casablanca on Wednesday. After completing their travel procedures at a hall dedicated to the initiative hall, the pilgrims told the Saudi Press Agency that the initiative contributed to alleviating their journey and facilitating travel procedures. They expressed their gratitude to the Kingdom for its services to pilgrims and for developing systems to enable pilgrims to perform Hajj with ease. The Makkah Route initiative is part of Saudi Arabia's Guests of God Service Program and seeks to provide visitors to the holy sites with the finest possible services to help them perform their Hajj rituals easily and comfortably.